<title>USA: Sodak Gaming Inc Q4 net declines.</title>
<headline>Sodak Gaming Inc Q4 net declines.</headline>
<dateline>RAPID CITY, S.D. 1997-02-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>($ amounts in millions, except earnings per share)</p>
<p>				   3 Months Ended     Year Ended</p>
<p>				     December 31,	December 31,</p>
<p>					1996   1995	 1996  1995</p>
<p>Product sales			18.5  24.7	104.5  73.2</p>
<p>Wide area progressive systems   2.2   1.4	  8.1   4.1</p>
<p>Domestic gaming operations	7.4   2.0	 20.2   8.2</p>
<p>International gaming operations 5.5   1.4	 15.8   2.3</p>
<p>Financing income and other	1.6   1.6	  6.0   5.5</p>
<p>Total Revenues		     35.2  31.1	154.6  93.3</p>
<p>Costs and expenses		 33.2  23.7	133.7  73.1</p>
<p>Income from operations	    2.0   7.4	 20.9  20.2</p>
<p>Earnings before income taxes    2.0   7.4	 20.9  20.3</p>
<p>Net earnings			  1.2   4.7	 13.2  12.9</p>
<p>Earnings per share		  0.05  0.21	0.58  0.57</p>
<p>Note: Earnings per share figures reflect the two-for-one stock split effective September 27, 1996.</p>
<p>Q4 1996 results hurt by delays in product sales shipments, severe weather in the upper Midwest, unanticipated increase in operating expenses relating to gaming operations in Peru and an increase in the allowance for doubtful accounts.</p>
<p>((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
